reviews.text:
We go here every year.

Check itabout you will learn a lot.
Nice variety of eras and styles of miniature doll houses. The museum is packed full of very detailed items that are worthy of being considered pieces of art.
$10.00 charge to visit.  Only ok.  Couldn't view all due to a meeting in progress blocking some displays.
The museum of minitures is one if the biggest adventures you can explore! Beyond awesome!

Loved it! 😊 Kid friendly (with supervision). I visited with my daughter and granddaughter, who is five years old. She was given a clipboard "treasure hunt" to fill out while I perused the collection and wallowed in forgotten childhood dreams. At the end of our experience she turned the finished sheet in for a prize and we chose some miniatures, carpets and wallpapers from the museum store to begin her own dollshouse. A wonderful experience.
This is a small little slice of Carmel History. The building is small only takes a short time to walk through, but it's a neat place to visit none the less.
Beautiful artwork and classic photos
A great group of people here, working to preserve Carmel's history!
Love history

The ambiance is sophisticated and festive. The servers are professional and knowledgeable, attentive without hovering. The food is incredible. I haven't eaten here for a few years, so I was delighted to find new dishes on the menu. My meal was perfectly seasoned and plated. I will eat here again!

Very romantic place for a random husband and wife date night. Our server was very knowledgeable and on top of his game. The food was amazing, we had an absolutely lovely time! Would def go back again to this location.

This restaurant greets you as an old friend.  Friendly, happy to answer any questions and polite.  Amanda was our waitress.  She was just perfect.  She anticipated our needs and was very attentive.   The food is out of this world.  From the stuffed mushrooms to the filet with caramelized scallops, the dining experience is the best. We will be back every time we visit our children.

To

Just enjoyed a wonderful meal with my girlfriend for a late valentines dinner. Our server Antonio had excellent recommendations for whiskey and food! Great place to go for a nice meal without totally breaking the bank! Thanks Antonio!

PHENOMENAL!!!

Scallops were incredible. Highly recommend! Request Matthew as your server, best service I have received in a long time.

Fresh Mexican fare with a very wide variety of choices. A lot of custom "choose your own" combos as well as traditional house specials. Not too heavy like a lot of greasy Mexican cuisine.  They bring you cups and 3 different flavorful salsas right away. The service is excellent. Our server went above and beyond for us and was incredibly polite.
Good stop over for a quick appetizer and drink. Good attentive service and priced right. Don't pass on the chicken nachos, but what I expected, better than the menu description. Enjoy
Food was delicious but above all was the AMAZING service we received from our server Austin and the rest of Abuelos staff. He was so truly genuine and down to earth. All around a great experience.
Great food with great charm. Lots of options and large menu. I like the decor of the restaurant. Well worth the money

One of my favorite Mexican restaurants. The food is authentic and delicious. I come here every time I'm in town. The service is always prompt and friendly. Start with the jalapeno fritters with ranch dip...so good!  The 5 enchiladas platter is my husband's favorite. I love it all so I'm working through the menu.
really great food in a comfortable environment.  would recommend to most everyone
Go here regularly   Great food and service.  There chips are the best I've ever had.

This was a great restaurant that is devised for people that like to share their food. The corn Chaucer was amazing along with the sliders and tacos. The food is presented in a very elegant way and it was fun to try all their different creations with each other. I would actually say that the prices are fair and the service is very good. They also have a very nice bar with some great cocktails. I had the new old fashioned and it was very tasty/boozy!
We had a group of 4 and tried all sorts of things. Loved most of the dishes and the ones we didn't like as much, we still finished the plate. Definitely more in the menu I'd like to try.

The hands-down most amazing mac and cheese I've ever had in my entire existence of life. Would go back here again if I was in a relationship for a date. The cucumber water makes me want to hang myself from a ceiling fan and turn it on high but honestly it's still an amazing restaurant. Food is amazing

We had a team dinner there.  The team at divvy set up the menu and took care of us all night.  The food was amazing, the service was top notch.   My team still talks about that night and wants to go back!
Great place, building is clean, staff is friendly and helpful. The food is delicious so visit with an appetite!!!!  we enjoyed everything we ordered. 🙌

The food is good. Not amazing but good. I got a burger and chive fries with a slice of Wicks Sugar Cream pie. The burger tasted really good but a little too thick for me. I was really excited about the chive fries & the texture is really good & crispy but they were a little bland. Definitely need dipping sauce. The pie is good of course it's Wicks. They sprinkle some cinnamon on it.

Great atmosphere, very good food, and excellent service. Reasonable prices too.
I was told that they're not open on Saturday or Sunday though.

Great place to meet for casual business meetings. Friendly staff and good food at a fair price. It's nice when the owner of an establishment is so involved and adheres to the adage, "I won't serve it if I wouldn't eat it".  It's also nice to see that it has found success for so long; since 1985. I recommend a stop in.
I've visited twice and the food is pretty good, but not amazing. The service we've had both times is great. My only complaint is that the restuarant feels dated and dingy.
Food is great and consistent. You have to try the tenderloin, it is the best in the state...

I went here on a Sunday which is happy hour all day. I got three sushi rolls which I thought were really nice sized. The sushi was above average tasting here and the atmosphere was nice. The deep discounts offered during happy hour make this a must try place! Note the happy hour is only valid if you sit at the bar or in the bar area!
Great customer service, great food, beautiful atmosphere. Very relaxing and nice music playing. Good prices and drinks. Definitely going back. Nice for date nights or girls night out.
Always a great experience eating here.  Good food.  Could turn down the music a bit, though.  I felt like I had to yell during my dinner conversation.

Got a chance to meet chef Pferron , love his energy to please his guest and the final result of our request. Mr. Jorge is and always a pleasure to have him serve us at the bar .he is wonderful. We visit here quite frequently and with these guys on board, we will keep returning to this location and time.

We visit this place several times a year. Food and service are always top notch. Menu changes from time to time but I always find something good. We were here on a Thursday and they had a half price wine special on bottles and you could take them home with you. It friends had the sea bass and it was excellent.
Veggie calzone was delicious and gigantic. Went on Tuesday for half off tall boy domestics and they had a great selection. Staff was friendly and attentive.
Great atmosphere with great service. You can't go wrong with this place. We ordered our food and we got it quick! Great selection of beers too!

We came from Georgia where I first encountered this chain. Over there the pizza was amazing. Simply to die for. And when we moved here I was so excited to see that there was a location near us. We drove from Lafayette to dine here because we loved the locations in Georgia so much. I was so disappointed. More like heartbroken. Our buffalo pizza stopped being made halfway up the pizza leaving a thick piece of crust. Our bbq chicken side was burnt. We asked for no onions on both sides there were onions. The crust was not like the other locations. It was hard. My son got the pretzel bites the only good thing that came to our table. It's what I expected my crust on my pizza to be. Our waitress forgot about us once it got busy. The host was the only reason this place got 2 stars. She was amazing and so friendly with my son. I think it needs to meet the management at other locations. Next time we will wait till I visit my in laws in Georgia. Such a huge let down. And dont tell me about it being burnt because it goes into an oven when 2 completely different locations have the same crust and same quality of food on the opposite sides of Georgia. There's something not right with this location.
A very clean  restaurant. Friendly staff not afraid to smile an say hello. Good food. Overall a pleasant experience
Great Pizza! Good servers with efficient service and decent serving time. Try the House special and the mighty meaty! The spinach dip is great too.

I had heard good things about Zeke's so I was super excited to try it out. To say the least, my experience was less than pleasant.

First off, they have some of the worst hours I have ever seen. Closed Sunday, Monday & Tuesday while only open half-days on Wednesday. I finally decided to go after work Thursday evening only to find they had, hands down the worst fried chicken I have ever had. 

The spices were perfect and tasty, fully coated, and very good. But the chicken itself was so dry and tough it was inedible. I do not know if my experience was a one-off thing, but there is no way in hell someone could get me to go there again. I honestly wonder if their chicken is so bad because they have to use a product which they must keep frozen 3 days a week?

If you want to, try it for yourself. I hope it is better for you than it was for me.

Truman

Ironically, I arrived here because the Burger King commercials had me craving a good hot dog.  Since I drive past this place almost every day I decided to stop in.  They actually have a pretty solid menu.  The food was excellent and it was cheap.  That's not even the best part though.  Each and every member of their staff treated me like I was family.  This is exactly what hospitality is all about.  Anytime I'm craving items they serve I'll be back again.  Thank you for this Zeke's because I feel this kind of service is becoming a lost art.
Only been once so far, but will be back.  Had the medium level Hot Chicken.  Very good.  Will go hot level next time.  Sides were very good.  Nice place, very casual..

Absolutely amazing place! We met the owner and he was friendly and engaging, along with the rest of the staff! The quality if food matched the quality of the atmosphere.  He has nailed the Chicago classics. The food was delicious and fresh.  We will be going back!

Great atmosphere. Great Staff. We met the owners and their daughters and they were all wonderful and very nice to talk to. The food was amazing too!! We had the Rib tips and pulled pork with macaroni and baked beans. The peach cobbler was to die for!!! We will happily drive from the south east side again for this place.

Nice place, but I expected a far better selection of unique candies and sweets.   Most of the candies I can obtain a a drug store.  Disappointing, since I traveled a far distance with hopes of more old-time and unique sweets.
